# choose-voice — set or browse the TTS voice for ListenClaude

ListenClaude's read-aloud uses one of three engines (system / piper / elevenlabs). This skill helps the user pick a voice from any of them and writes the choice to `.env` so it takes effect on the next response.

## How to interpret the user's request

| User intent | Action |
|---|---|
| "list system voices" / "macOS voices" / "SAPI voices" | List built-in OS voices (see below). |
| "open ElevenLabs library" / "browse voices" | Tell the user to open https://elevenlabs.io/app/voice-library, audition, and copy a voice_id. |
| "list my ElevenLabs voices" | Call ElevenLabs API to list voices saved in their account. Requires `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` in `.env`. |
| "use voice <id>" / "set voice to <name>" / "switch to <id>" | Run `set-voice.{ps1,sh}` with the voice ID. Detect engine from format: hex-ish 20-char string = elevenlabs; `.onnx` or `zh_CN-*` = piper; otherwise system. Pass the engine as second arg when changing. |
| "what voice am I using" / "current voice" | Read TTS_VOICE and TTS_ENGINE from `__REPO_DIR__/.env`. |

## Listing voices

### System (macOS)
```
say -v '?' | grep -E 'zh|en'
```

### System (Windows)
```
powershell "Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Speech; (New-Object System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer).GetInstalledVoices().VoiceInfo | Select Name,Culture"
```

### Piper
List files in `~/.cache/piper-voices/*.onnx` (or `$PIPER_VOICES_DIR`). Direct user to https://rhasspy.github.io/piper-samples/ for previews / downloads.

### ElevenLabs (user's saved voices)
```bash
curl -s -H "xi-api-key: $ELEVENLABS_API_KEY" https://api.elevenlabs.io/v1/voices | jq '.voices[] | {voice_id, name, labels}'
```

### ElevenLabs (community library)
Tell the user to open https://elevenlabs.io/app/voice-library in their browser — that page has live preview which an API call cannot match.

## Setting the voice

**Windows:**
```
powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "__REPO_DIR__\scripts\set-voice.ps1" -VoiceId <id> [-Engine <engine>]
```

**macOS / Linux:**
```
bash "__REPO_DIR__/scripts/set-voice.sh" <id> [<engine>]
```

`<engine>` is `system`, `piper`, or `elevenlabs`. Omit if the engine is already configured correctly.

After setting, echo back the new `TTS_ENGINE` and `TTS_VOICE` values (the script prints them). No restart needed — the next Claude response will use the new voice.
